adjectives.description: shockproof (comparative more shockproof, superlative most shockproof)

entries.meaning: Made sturdily enough to withstand knocks and shocks without being damaged.
examples: My shockproof watch stood up to everything it reasonably could be expected to and kept ticking; but dropping it down an elevator shaft is asking too much.

verbs.description: shockproof (third-person singular simple present shockproofs, present participle shockproofing, simple past and past participle shockproofed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To protect from imparting electric shocks.
